Below is one workable reading of the picture and a matching set of blocks (by index) together with a sensible build‐order.  The description is divided into three parts, following the prompt:

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1)  DESCRIPTION OF THE MAIN TARGET IMAGE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
•  Overall Count and Layers
   – There are 20 total blocks split into two main groupings (a left “tower” assembly of 9 pieces and a right “arched‐wall” assembly of 11 pieces).
   – Both groupings are built in (at least) two layers.  The left tower stacks cylinders and horizontal beams topped with triangular “roof” wedges; the right grouping has two red arches on the bottom layer with cubes/half‐cylinders/rectangular blocks above them and three tall yellow columns at the back.

•  Left‐Side “Tower” Assembly (9 blocks)
   – Base:
     1) Two orange cylinders stand on the ground (a tall column of three stacked cylinders on the left, and a single cylinder on the right).
   – Mid‐Level:
     2) Two yellow rectangular prisms form a “T” shape bridging across the columns (one oriented left‐to‐right, the other front‐to‐back).
     3) A smaller yellow rectangular block protrudes from this T‐shaped portion.
   – Top:
     4) Two orange triangular wedges (roofs): one sits atop the tall cylinder; the other atop the horizontal yellow T‐beam.

•  Right‐Side “Arched Wall” Assembly (11 blocks)
   – Base:
     1) Two red arches side by side.
   – Front Row Above the Arches:
     2) From left to right: one blue cube, one green rectangular block, two yellow half‐cylinders, another green rectangular block, and one orange cube.
   – Rear Row:
     3) Three tall yellow rectangular pillars stand behind (and slightly above) the front‐row blocks.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2)  BLOCK‐SELECTION FROM THE DICTIONARY
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Below are all 20 required blocks (with the exact orientations shown in the dictionary).  The same index is repeated if that shape/orientation is used multiple times.

● Left‐Side Tower (9 pieces)
   (a)  Four cylinders, index 11
   (b)  One yellow rectangular prism (left‐right), index 7
   (c)  One yellow rectangular prism (front‐back), index 8
   (d)  One small yellow rectangular block, index 13
   (e)  Two orange triangular wedges, index 16

● Right‐Side Arched Wall (11 pieces)
   (a)  Two red arches, index 1
   (b)  One blue cube, index 3
   (c)  Two green rectangular blocks (horizontal), index 6
   (d)  Two yellow half‐cylinders, index 12
   (e)  One orange cube, index 4
   (f)  Three tall yellow rectangular pillars, index 10

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3)  STEP‐BY‐STEP ASSEMBLY INSTRUCTIONS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Below is one possible bottom‐to‐top build order.  Simply list the moves in order, using the required indices:

{
  Step1:  Move block with index 11
